INTRODUCTION

CAMPSITE is a content management system with multi-lingual
Unicode support, designed for medium to large sized online
publications. Issues, back archives, as well as subscription
management are fully implemented features. At the core of
management system sits the CAMPFIRE, a Java program supporting
Unicode fonts, allowing contributors and editors to control
layout online in their native font face. Style features can be
assigned via buttons - similar to editors such as Wordpad -
meaning no HTML knowledge is necessary for formatting text.

We encourage further development of this software and would
like to make any progress accessible to all other users.
Please contact us if you have or intend to developed this
software further.

CAMPSITE offers...
-  support of managing article translations in different
   languages
-  advanced editorial interface for remote article editing
-  cut and paste formatting from other editors into the online
-  Java Editor for HTML with near WYSIWYG feel (CAMPFIRE)
-  its own customizable search-engine
-  built-in subscription system
-  management of dictionaries

CREDITS

The original CAMPSITE concept was developed by C@MP in
collaboration with Transitions Online, who started using
CAMPSITE in late 2000. Coding and further development was
accomplished by DNT and Recognos.

