TECH-SPECS

Implementing CAMPSITE for your purposes requires the following
technical set-up, nothing out of the ordinary.

CAMPSITE server:
- runs on a Linux server, tested with RedHat 7.0 and Mandrake 8.0
- needs an Apache web to be running, and its virtual servers
  configured by the administrator.
- for data storage it is needed a MySQL database server for
  Linux. The tests were made on MySQL v.3.23.36.

CAMPSITE client:
- tested on Netscape under Unix, Macintosh and Windows,
  Internet Explorer under Windows.
- has a client Editor interface implemented as a Java Applet
  (browser-compatibility reason).
- copy the file swingall.jar in the Java classes directory
  (see http://www.campware.org).
- unpack the file unicoded.zip in the same Java classes
  directory (see http://www.campware.org).

Note: Client site preparation will be made redundant with the
evolution of browsers, since this module becomes native in
built-in Java Virtual Machines. The file is distributed freely
and native with the JDK 1.2 package.

WORKING DEMO

CAMPSITE in action can be seen at the Transitions Online
website (http://www.tol.cz). However, there is a version
implemented at campware for testing purposes. Contact us for
login information: contact@campware.org

COPYRIGHT

CAMPSITE is a Unicode-enabled multilingual web content
management system for news publications.
CAMPFIRE is a Unicode-enabled java-based near WYSIWYG text editor.
